"line in the middle is the typical age at death (the median). The box itself "
"covers the middle 50 %% of the cohort — its lower edge is the age below "
"which a quarter died (P25), its upper edge the age below which three "
"quarters died (P75). The thin lines extending up and down (the \"whiskers\") "
"reach the youngest and oldest typical case; individual dots beyond the "
"whiskers are rare extreme cases — very young child deaths at the bottom, "
"centenarians at the top. Cohorts smaller than five individuals are hidden "
"because a single life cannot represent a century."
